# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Overview

A full-stack application with a Next.js frontend, Elysia API backend, and PostgreSQL database.

## Project Structure

```
├── frontend/     # Next.js web app (port 3000)
├── backend/      # Elysia API (port 3001)
├── shared/       # Shared TypeScript types
└── docker-compose.yml
```

## Development

- Frontend dev server runs on port 3000 inside its container
- Backend API runs on port 3001 inside its container
- PostgreSQL is available at `postgres:5432` inside Docker
- Use TypeScript for all new files

### Frontend

- Place components in `frontend/src/components/`
- Place utilities in `frontend/src/lib/`
- API calls go through `frontend/src/lib/api-client.ts`

### Backend

- Place routes in `backend/src/routes/`
- Place business logic in `backend/src/services/`
- Use Prisma for database access

## Commands

### Frontend

```bash
cd frontend && npm run dev     # Start dev server
cd frontend && npm run lint    # Run ESLint
```

### Backend

```bash
cd backend && bun run dev      # Start dev server
cd backend && bun run lint     # Run ESLint
cd backend && bunx prisma migrate dev  # Create a migration
```
